---
---

<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 800px;">
    <div class="text-center mb-5">
      <div class="badge-container mb-3" style="display: inline-block; background-color: rgba(82, 206, 199, 0.12); border-radius: 50px; padding: 0.35rem 1.25rem; border: 1px solid rgba(82, 206, 199, 0.25);">
        <span style="font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; color: #52CEC7; text-transform: uppercase;">Got Questions?</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h1 text-white">Startups Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-accordion">
      <details class="faq-item" open>
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            <span class="faq-q-badge">?</span>
            What exactly is an engineering "pod"?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          It is a dedicated group of developers, UX designers, and DevOps engineers who work as a single team on your product. Instead of managing multiple freelance contracts or employees, you manage a single channel.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            <span class="faq-q-badge">?</span>
            Who owns the intellectual property (IP)?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          You do. 100% of the repository, design assets, and cloud deployment code belongs to your startup from day one. We deliver a complete handover when you are ready to hire in-house.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            <span class="faq-q-badge">?</span>
            How fast can we launch our MVP?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          Most startup MVPs (including backend API database architectures, user profiles, dashboard analytics, and custom AI plugins) are completed and deployed to live servers within 4 to 8 weeks.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="faq-question-content">
            <span class="faq-q-badge">?</span>
            Are there long-term contracts?
          </span>
          <svg class="faq-chevron" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          No. We work on rolling monthly agreements. Startups need agility; you can scale the pod up, down, or pause services with a 14-day notice.
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
